    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-30T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-30T16:00:00-05:00" n="615"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d615">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense (M) Chile/61: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-30T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >December 30, 1941—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>851. The signature of the overall purchase agreement is merely awaiting approval
                    by Chilean Congress of copper tax proposal which the Minister of Finance hopes
                    may be forthcoming within the next few days. The Chilean authorities are very
                    anxious to close the agreement as soon as possible.<note n="88" xml:id="d615fn1"
                        >The agreement was completed by an exchange of notes on January 26,
                        1942.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bowers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
